; Associated deities
* {{ill|lt=Emperor Kōrei|Q313041|qid=Q313041|lt=Ōyamato Nekohikofutoni no Mikoto|1=Emperor Kōrei}}
* {{ill|lt=Kibitsuhiko-no-Mikoto|Q65318|qid=Q65318|1=Kibitsuhiko-no-mikoto}}

=== History ===
This shrine is identified with Mishima Shrine in Mishima District of {{ill|lt=Echigo Province|Q666514|qid=Q666514|1=Echigo Province}}, listed as a Shikinaisha in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} compiled in {{ill|lt=927|Q30470|qid=Q30470|1=927}}<ref>{{Cite book|和書|editor=教部省|author=|year=1925|title={{ill|lt=Tokusen Jinmeichō|Q11571092|qid=Q11571092|1=Tokusen Jinmyōchō}}|publisher=磯部甲陽堂|page=|isbn=|ref=}}</ref>. It was invited from {{ill|lt=Ōyamazumi Shrine|Q703904|qid=Q703904|1=Ōyamazumi Shrine}} on {{ill|lt=Ōmishima|Q9009869|qid=Q9009869|1=Ōmishima Island}} in {{ill|lt=Iyo Province|Q907829|qid=Q907829|1=Iyo Province}}, and is traditionally said to have been founded in {{ill|lt=741|Q23597|qid=Q23597|1=741}}<ref name=柏崎市三島神社/>.

It received devotion from the {{ill|lt=Usami clan|Q24860892|qid=Q24860892|1=Usami clan}}, then from the {{ill|lt=Echigo Nagao clan|Q1655561|qid=Q1655561|lt=Echigo Nagao clan|1=Nagao clan}} (Uesugi clan), and successive lords of the {{ill|lt=Takada Domain|Q839422|qid=Q839422|1=Takada Domain}}<ref name=柏崎市三島神社>[https://www.city.kashiwazaki.lg.jp/soshikiichiran/sangyoshinkobu/shogyokankoka/kankosinko/23/25/3/3627.html 柏崎市名所案内「三島神社(みしまじんじゃ)」]（Kashiwazaki City）</ref>. According to the {{ill|lt=Tokusen Jinmeichō|Q11571092|qid=Q11571092|1=Tokusen Jinmyōchō}}, it was originally in Mishimatani village five ri east of Ishiji Station, and later moved to the current site.

In {{ill|lt=1873|Q7757|qid=Q7757|1=1873}} it became a prefectural shrine. However, due to later fire, it no longer retains the former appearance<ref name=柏崎市三島神社/>. The current shrine buildings were rebuilt in 1931<ref name=柏崎市三島神社/>.

In {{ill|lt=1973|Q2477|qid=Q2477|1=1973}}, it was designated a city cultural property (monument, historic site)<ref name=柏崎市三島神社/>.

